3 Statistical tests

The unpaired two-samples Wilcoxon test (also known as Wilcoxon rank sum test or Mann-Whitney U test, Mann-Whitney Wilcoxon test) It is a non-parametric alternative to the unpaired two-samples t-test, which can be used to compare two independent groups of samples. It’s used when your data are not normally distributed.

library(rstatix)
## 
## Attaching package: 'rstatix'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter
stat.test1 <- df1 %>%
  rstatix::group_by(glycan) %>%
  rstatix::wilcox_test(value ~ LFA15) %>%
  rstatix::adjust_pvalue(method = "BH") %>%
  rstatix::add_significance() %>%
  rstatix::add_y_position() %>%
  rstatix::add_x_position(x = "glycan")

stat.test2 <- df2 %>%
  rstatix::group_by(glycan) %>%
  rstatix::wilcox_test(value ~ FFA15) %>%
  rstatix::adjust_pvalue(method = "BH") %>%
  rstatix::add_significance() %>%
  rstatix::add_y_position() %>%
  rstatix::add_x_position(x = "glycan", dodge = 1)
